    <title>Reusable Components</title>
    <body>
        <p>
            <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_qzx_k32_scb">
                <title>Here are reusable components</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Description</entry>
                            <entry>Content</entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Disclaimer</entry>
                            <entry>
                                <p>
                                    <note id="rc-css-fragment-disclaimer-note">This is listed for exemplification
                                        purposes, the plugin might use something different.</note>
                                </p>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Chapter definition</entry>
                            <entry>
                                <note id="note_x1s_2f2_5cb">For a plain DITA map, the chapters are the topic elements
                                    that are placed on the first level for bookmaps the chapters are the topics referred
                                    by a chapter element. </note>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Do not edit styles from the installation directory</entry>
                            <entry>
                                <note type="caution" id="note_gxm_jyq_5cb">Do not modify the builtin rules from the CSS
                                    files from the oXygen installation. Instead copy the rules in your customization
                                    CSS.</note>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>SVG recommandation.</entry>
                            <entry>
                                <note id="note_pqy_hdn_vcb">You can use raster image formats like PNG, JPEG, but it is
                                    best to use vector images, that can be scaled and give a much better result when
                                    printed: SVG, PDF.</note>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </p>
    </body>
